<TITLE> Court frames charges against former secy Akhtar Hossain </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 9 (bdnews24.com)  A Dhaka special judge's court Tuesday framed charges against former power secretary ANH Akhtar Hossain and his wife Nazneen Banu in a corruption case. Judge Amar Kumar Roy of Special Judge's Court-2 housed on the Sangsad Bhaban premises also set Oct 17 for recording witnesses' depositions. Prosecution witnesses in the case number 31. Anticorruption Commission assistant director Mahabubul Alam filed the case against the Akhtar couple on March 31 with Uttara Police Station. The case details said Akhtar acquired illegal wealth valued at Tk 2.15 crore through misuse of office. Akhtar had also concealed information on assets worth Tk 80 lakh in his wealth statement submitted to the ACC. His wife Nazneen abetted him in all these illegal activities, the case alleged. Joint forces arrested Akhtar on Feb 25 as he was coming out of the ACC headquarters after submitting a wealth statement. His wife is on the run. On Feb 18, the ACC published a list of 50 graft suspects including politicians, businessmen, bureaucrats and other professionals. It asked the suspects, including Akhtar, to submit statements of wealth owned by them and their family members within 72 hours of the publication of the same. bdnews
